<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-22T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-22T10:00:00-05:00" n="232" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d232">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.5111/672: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Deputy Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>(<hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>) <hi rend="smallcaps">Bordeaux</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-22T17:00:00+02:00">June 22, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 11:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>72. For the President. Reynaud is deeply touched by your personal message
                            and asks me to convey to you an expression of his profound appreciation.
                            He is happy thus to learn that you are aware of his fight to continue
                            resistance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>